#MEM id=lena source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/lena/MEMORY-hourbour.md
M|lena|> Load alongside mem.md when active vtr is Hourbour.
M|lena|> Hourbour-specific ctx only — universal rules live in mem.md.
M|lena|- **Model**: Fintech SaaS subscription (B2C/B2B)
M|lena|- **Voice**: trustworthy, modern, approachable — plain English, no jargon
M|lena|- **Audience**: people who want clarity and control over their money, not fin nerds
M|lena|- **Never say**: complicated, risky, complex, volatile, bet, gamble, wealth
M|lena|- **Never use**: fin-bro language, excessive acronyms, fear-based messaging
M|lena|- **Do say**: clear, simple, trackable, reliable, automatic, in control
M|lena|- **Sentence style**: short, active voice — "See exactly where your money goes." not "Our platform provides comprehensive financial visibility."
M|lena|- **Emoji**: 1 max per post; prefer functional (📊, ✅) over decorative
M|lena|| Platform | Length | Format |
M|lena||----------|--------|--------|
M|lena|| LinkedIn | 3–5 lines | Hook + specific insight + question or CTA |
M|lena|| Instagram | 2–3 lines | Plain-English hook + one clear benefit |
M|lena|| Email subject | ≤9 words | Specific, not clever ("Your April spending, visualised") |
M|lena|| YouTube description | 2–3 sentences | Purpose + CTA + link |
M|lena|> Populated from high-performing copy. Each entry: [date] — hook — what made it work.
M|lena|> Each entry: [date] — Hourbour-specific copy error — rule.